==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: moulding
<hw>moulding</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>a sculpture produced by
molding.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> mold, mould, molding, modeling, clay
sculpture.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>a decorative recessed or relieved surface.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> molding, border.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>a decorative strip used for ornamentation or
finishing.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> molding.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>a preliminary sculpture in wax or clay from which a
finished work can be copied.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> modeling, molding.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

